This Zeppelin Notebook shows how to use Chronix to analyze and visualize time series data.

paragraphs.title: Create RDD, calculate statistics & create sQL Table
paragraphs.text:
%spark
import de.qaware.chronix.spark.api.java.ChronixSparkContext
import org.apache.spark.api.java.JavaSparkContext
import org.apache.solr.client.solrj.SolrQuery
import de.qaware.chronix.storage.solr.ChronixSolrCloudStorage

// Create RDD
val csc = new ChronixSparkContext(new JavaSparkContext(sc))
val query = new SolrQuery("*:*")
val rdd = csc.query(query, "localhost:9983", "chronix", new ChronixSolrCloudStorage())

// Calculate statistics (number of overall observations)
rdd.countObservations()

// Create DataFrame and register table
val timeseries = rdd.toDataFrame(sqlContext)
timeseries.registerTempTable("timeseries")

paragraphs.title: read and visualize timeseries with SQL
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select timestampObject, value, process, metric 
from timeseries 
where process="global" and metric="\\CPU\\us"
order by timestampObject

%sql
select timestampObject, value, process, metric 
from timeseries 
where metric="\\Memory\\free" or metric="\\CPU\\us"
order by timestamp
